{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb95ce15a-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2313"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2313"},"text":"§ 2313.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Sale or receipt of stolen vehicles","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb95ce15b-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2313/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Whoever receives, possesses, conceals, stores, barters, sells, or disposes of any motor vehicle, vessel, or aircraft, which has crossed a State or United States boundary after being stolen, knowing the same to have been stolen, shall be fined under this title or imprisoned not more than 10 years, or both.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb95ce15c-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2313/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" For purposes of this section, the term “State” includes a State of the United States, the District of Columbia, and any commonwealth, territory, or possession of the United States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb95ce15d-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 645","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/806"},"text":"62 Stat. 806","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/547/tII/s203"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–547, title II, § 203","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-10-25"},"text":"Oct. 25, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/2770"},"text":"98 Stat. 2770","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/647/tXII/s1205"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–647, title XII, § 1205","children":[],"tail":"("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/4831"},"text":"104 Stat. 4831","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/519/tI/s103"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–519, title I, § 103","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-25"},"text":"Oct. 25, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/3385"},"text":"106 Stat. 3385","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/177/tIII/s307/b/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–177, title III, § 307(b)(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-03-09"},"text":"Mar. 9, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/240"},"text":"120 Stat. 240","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb95ce15e-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb95ce15f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on title 18, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 408 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1919-10-29/ch89/s4"},"text":"Oct. 29, 1919, ch. 89, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/41/325"},"text":"41 Stat. 325","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1945-09-24/ch383"},"text":"Sept. 24, 1945, ch. 383","children":[],"tail":", §§ 2, 3, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/59/536"},"text":"59 Stat. 536","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section constitutes the fourth sentence of said ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s408"},"text":"section 408 of title 18","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Definitions of “aircraft,” “motor vehicle,” and “interstate or foreign commerce,” which constituted the second sentence of said section 408, are incorporated in sections 10 and 2311 of this title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The third sentence of said section 408, relating to transporting stolen aircraft or motor vehicles, is incorporated in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s2312"},"text":"section 2312 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The first sentence of said section 408, providing the short title, and the fifth sentence thereof, relating to venue, were omitted. (See reviser’s note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s2312"},"text":"section 2312 of this title","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Minor changes were made in phraseology.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb95ce160-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb95ce161-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/177"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–177","children":[],"tail":" substituted “motor vehicle, vessel, or aircraft” for “motor vehicle or aircraft”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1992—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/519"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–519","children":[],"tail":" substituted “fined under this title or imprisoned not more than 10 years” for “fined not more than $5,000 or imprisoned not more than five years”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/647"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–647","children":[],"tail":" designated existing provisions as subsec. (a) and added subsec. (b)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/547"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–547","children":[],"tail":" inserted “possesses,” after “receives,” and substituted “which has crossed a State or United States boundary after being stolen,” for “moving as, or which is a part of, or which constitutes interstate or foreign commerce,”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
